			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zarath wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You don't offtank without your pet? I would assume the character is a better offtank due to the ability to, you know, hold aggro over other players. The bottom line is a Beastlord is not designed to have the best pet, even the best all around pet. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm talking about high end, friend.  If you have played there (not so sure after reading your posts),  you realize, that with Elementals + pets did not scale with mobs?  Any raid that uses a beastloord (without pet) as an offtank is a doomed raid.  I don't believe you have a clue as to what beastlords were designed for.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">It's basic class balance. Mages need a pet with mitigation enough to offset the lack of slow and damage enough to be in line with Mages being a "respectable damage dealer". IF a Beastlord gets a pet that is able to mitigate as well as a Mage pet then they would be overpowered due to their ability to slow. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Mages need a pet that can mitigate so that the mage can burn the mob down.  Most of the battles are not, therefore no slow is needed, due to the high DPS a mage puts out (compared to a beastlord).
<br />

<br />
A beastlord needs a pet that can mitigate well enough, so that when coupled with pet heals, the mob can be killed.  Takes alot longer than a mage kill, due to much lower DPS.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">In my above heirarchy, the Warder would do less DPS then air and tank just about as well, pretty much where it is now. However when a boost to the Mage's pet is put in to help balance the class why must Beastlords ask for it too? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">  
<br />

<br />
For the same reason that mages want it.  Pets do not scale with the new release of mobs.  Now, since I answered you, try answering my question...  How would it negatively impact a mage if beastlord pets mitigation were raised?  We do not compete for the same group spots.
<br />

