				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ignoring your inflammatorycomments, using your logic against beastlords, why would MS4 need it mitigation upgraded for group friendliness? Since you said a warder does not need it in groups...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Churizo,
<br />

<br />
The MS4 pets needs some kind of reason to exist/ be used.  It's current purpose of raid pet is almost comical.  Given a choice on a raid between a pet with nearly zero push,  a nonconfusing model, and excellent dps (water) and a pet with lower dps, a confusing model, and lots of push (stun+kick) I'm going to pick the water pet even with MSIV absorbing one wave of AOE.
<br />

<br />
The issue is not one of mage balance so much as that the MSIV in its current incarnation isn't terribly useful, and it should be more useful.   .
<br />

<br />
There are a number of ways you could make the pet more useful:
<br />

<br />
Stun proc + snare cast = solo pet
<br />
No kick, no stun, high damage lure spell, lots of hp, rune proc, and pre shrunk air pet model = raid pet
<br />
Stun, lots of hp, good mitigation, high aggro = a tank pet for nontraditional groups 
<br />

<br />
Any of the three would be fine with me.  As it is we have a mish mash of abilities that don't make any sense as a whole.  However, giving it earth like mitigation would make it useful and would make it an actual upgrade instead of a very situational pet, which isn't even very useful for situation it was supposedly designed for.  Don't get me wrong, I'm ok with situational abilities, but its not like the new wizard nuke upgrade whitefire is a situtional upgrade. It's a straight upgrade.  The MSIV pet should be a straight upgrade over our existing pets as well: 
<br />

<br />
Near Water pet dps, with Air Stun, Earth Hp/Mitigation would be a pet I would actually use as opposed to the current spell.<br />_________________<br />Traigos Ode
<br />
Arch Convoker
